## PROJECT TYPE
Healthcare documentation system for Ontario PSWs (Personal Support Workers)
- Next.js 16 + React 19 + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS
- Voice + AI-powered documentation
- Generates DAR (Data-Action-Response) JSON
- HIPAA-compliant, Ontario PSW standards

## CRITICAL RULES

### 1. BRAND COLORS (USE EVERYWHERE)
- Navy Blue: #1B365D (primary)
- Gold: #D4A574 (accent)
- Light BG: #E8F0F5
- NEVER use random colors

### 2. VARIABLE NAMES (WILL CRASH IF WRONG)
‚úÖ CORRECT: report (state variable)
‚ùå WRONG: generatedReport (does NOT exist - causes ReferenceError)

Main component: components/PSWVoiceReporter.js
State: const [report, setReport] = useState('')

### 3. ONTARIO PSW SCOPE (CRITICAL)
PSWs can only OBSERVE and DOCUMENT. They CANNOT:
- ‚ùå Make medical diagnoses
- ‚ùå Do clinical assessments
- ‚ùå Prescribe or recommend treatments
- ‚ùå Use terms: diagnose, assess, prescribe, treatment plan

‚úÖ They CAN:
- Observe and record facts
- Document care activities (ADLs)
- Record client quotes
- Note vital signs if observed
- Write "Notify supervisor/RN" for concerns

